summary: it legit kills me to think peter was one of tony’s main motivations to want to try the time travel. that his first thought when...
body: it legit kills me to think peter was one of tony’s main motivations to want to try the time travel. that his first thought when he reunited with the others was “i lost the kid”. it kills me to think how happy he was when he saw peter again he almost couldnt believe it, and hugging him so dearly. peter telling him “please don’t go” was so heartwrenching to watch. it surely was sad and it brought me to tears but i was truly overwhelmed with joy of how much tony cared for peter like he was his own son and viceversa.

summary: No matter how much Marvel wants to change the status quo around from time to time, Black Cat is always gonna be an antiheroine. ...
body: No matter how much Marvel wants to change the status quo around from time to time, Black Cat is always gonna be an antiheroine. Which is one of the main reasons why her becoming a crime boss was an awful development for her character. Now that it’s finally over with, can we actually try to keep her more consistent and maybe turn into a full fledged superheroine someday? Like she could be a great inspiration for other thieves who are only trying to make ends meet and survive living. She could show that everyone can change.
